  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Clinic Assistant",
  "description": "<p><strong>Job Scope</strong></p><ul><li>Managing clinic reception (Registering patients, responding to enquiries, coordinating appointments, dispensing medication, payment collection)</li><li>Assist in insurance claims and coordination with insurance companies</li><li>Provide advice on pre and post procedure care</li><li>Maintain the cleanliness and order of consultation room and general areas</li><li>Follow-up with patients post procedure and to monitor their progress</li><li>Managing stock and keeping track of inventory</li><li>Assisting the doctor during consultation, surgical, medical and aesthetic procedures</li><li>Cross coverage for other colleagues when they are on leave</li></ul><p><strong>Requirements</strong></p><ul><li>Experience with front desk and customer service duties in a private clinic setting preferred</li><li>Dermatology experience preferred</li><li>Being a team player is critical</li><li>Good interpersonal skills to provide customer service confidently</li><li>Able to perform administrative duties with computer skills</li><li>Able to converse and write in English</li></ul><p><strong>Working Hours</strong></p><ul><li>Monday to Friday: 9am - 6pm</li><li>Saturday: 9am- 1pm</li></ul><p><strong>Benefits:</strong></p><ul><li>Competitive Salary with AWS</li><li>Performance-based incentives</li><li>Supportive and nurturing work environment.</li><li>Opportunities for career growth and advancement</li><li>Employee discounts on treatments and products</li><li>Central location near Orchard MRT</li></ul>",
